snippet.textDisplay:
I think it's kinda early to jump to conclusions. One game does not define the outcome of an entire season. LR haven't started scrimming LEC teams before this game, so we probably will see an improvement once scrims get underway. 

They also have a new head coach (coincidentally KC's ex-head coach). Everyone said they couldn't win EMEA three times, yet that still happened. It might be a rocky start but I'm confident they will adapt and perform well.

snippet.textDisplay:
I have no idea why Baus plays kled
He has poor clear speed, he has low damage, he is no tank, his ulti is the worst in top lane , his 1v1 is meh at best, he does not synergies with anything on the team, he is super dependent on getting ahead, if he gets behind he is more useless than river shen and provides nothing except a meat shield.
He has poor proxy potential, he has poor escape potential, if he demount you are literally 3/4 of a champ thats is on top of that crippled.

A rumble is everything a kled wishes to be.
